JWT validation Action 

resource "aws_lb_listener" "this"{
  load_balancer_arn =var.load_balancer_arn 
  port = "443"
  protocol = "HTTPS"
  ssl_policy = "ELBSecurityPolicy-2016-08"
  certificate_arn = var.certificate_arn 
  
  default_action {
    type = "jwt-validation"
    jwt-validation {
      issuer =  "https://example.com"
      jwks_endpoint = "https://example.com/.well-known/jwks.json"
      additional_claim {
        format = "string-array"
        name   = "claim_name1"
        values = ["value1", "value2"]
      }
      additional_claim {
        format = "single-string"
        name   = "claim_name2"
        values = ["value1"]
      }
      }
  }

  default_action {
    target_group_arn = aws_lb_target_group.test.id
    type             = "forward"
  }
}

Client connects to ALB (HTTPS)
Client sends JWT token in request

ALB checks:
👉 “Is this token from the correct issuer?”
ALB fetches keys from JWKS endpoint
ALB verifies:
👉 “Is this token signature valid?”
ALB checks claims:
👉 “Does this user have required permissions?”
If valid → request forwardedIf invalid → ❌ request rejected

