Required : 

default_action = tells what to do when the request is received and where to forward it 
load_balancer_arn = this is to tell to which load_balancer the listener is connected to 




Optional : 

region : tell where the resource will be managed  .Default to the region set in the provider configuration 

alpn_policy : Name of the Application layer protocol negotiation policy  , can be set if the protocol is TLS .Valid values are HTTP1Only, HTTP2Only, HTTP2Optional, HTTP2Preferred, and None

certificate_arn : arn of the certificate for encryption 

mutual_authentication : this block is used to configure mutual authenication information where both the user and server will exchange the certificate and  encrypt the communication between them 

port = the port throught which the listener listen , not valid for the gateway load balancer

protocol = the protocol for connection between the client and the load_balancer 
           for the application load_balancer the valid values are HTTP and HTTPS ,with default of HTTP .For the network loadbalancers .valid values are TCP,TLS ,UPD,TCP_UDP ,QUIC and TCP_QUIC .Not valid to use UPD AND TCP_UDP if the dual stack mode is enabled  . Not valid to use QUIC or TCP_QUIC if security groups are configured or dual stakc mode is enabled . Not valid for gateway load_balaners


ssl_policy : how to encrypt using the certificate , required if the  protocol is HTTPS and TLS  . default is ELBSecurityPolicy-2016-08.

tcp_idle_timeout_seconds : can be only set if the protocol is  TCP on NETWORK LOAD_BALANCERS  or with gateway load_balancers .Not supported for application load balancers . valid values are between the 60 and 6000



